cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the application of pre-trained convolutional neural network (CNN) architectures to the task of periocular recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), and the use of off-the-shelf CNN features, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves biometric recognition, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
